T1  - On Being Positive: Concerns and Counterpoints
AU  - Fineman, Stephen
Y1  - 2006/04/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.20208680
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2006.20208680
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 270
EP  - 291
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this article I examine the attractions and shortcomings of the ?positive? neohumanisitic turn in organizational theorizing and how positivity might be developed. I evaluate positivity's moral and cultural underpinnings and claims to separate positive from negative emotions, and I explore the deployment of positiveness in HRM programs of empowerment, emotional intelligence, and fun at work. I conclude with suggestions on how positive scholarship could be reconfigured in light of the present critique and against the emancipatory ideas of critical organizational theory.
AB  - In this article I examine the attractions and shortcomings of the ?positive? neohumanisitic turn in organizational theorizing and how positivity might be developed. I evaluate positivity's moral and cultural underpinnings and claims to separate positive from negative emotions, and I explore the deployment of positiveness in HRM programs of empowerment, emotional intelligence, and fun at work. I conclude with suggestions on how positive scholarship could be reconfigured in light of the present critique and against the emancipatory ideas of critical organizational theory.
